					<div class="col-md-5">
						<h6 class="tags">Workbench</h6>
						<h2><a href="http://www.nutsvolts.com/magazine/article/february2011_goodsell" style="color:#333">Build a Wall Wart Power Monitor</a></h2>
						<p><p>As an experimenter, I use wall warts all the time to power circuit boards, microcontroller boards, and even finished projects. However, during the checkout phase of a new circuit, wall warts present a problem. How do you measure their output when they&rsquo;re plugged into a board or project box?</p></p>
